-------------------------------------------------------------------
SECTION 1 — Identify All Delta Writes
-------------------------------------------------------------------

Find every occurrence of:

- df.write.format("delta")
- saveAsTable
- mode("overwrite") / mode("append")
- DeltaTable.forPath
- MERGE INTO

For each Delta write:
- File
- Line number
- Dataset name or path
- Estimated rows written
- Estimated data size
- Whether inside loop
- Whether inside group execution

Count:
Total Delta writes per job execution path.

-------------------------------------------------------------------
SECTION 2 — Trace Delta Read-After-Write Patterns
-------------------------------------------------------------------

For each Delta write detected:

Check if the same path or table is:

- Read later in same notebook
- Read in another notebook
- Read for Mongo conversion
- Read for Excel generation
- Read only for final aggregation

For each read-after-write:
- Identify code location
- Determine purpose (Mongo, Excel, aggregation, etc.)
- Determine if data was already available in memory before write
- Flag if write-read is unnecessary

-------------------------------------------------------------------
SECTION 3 — Determine Real Overhead Per Job
-------------------------------------------------------------------

For each Delta round-trip detected:

Estimate:

1. Data size (rows × estimated row size)
2. Write time cost (seconds)
3. Read time cost (seconds)
4. Extra Spark job triggered?
5. Extra shuffle stage introduced?
6. Commit protocol overhead?
7. Metadata overhead?

Compute:
Total Delta overhead per job (actual, not assumed).

-------------------------------------------------------------------
SECTION 4 — Detect Delta Used Only for Format Conversion
-------------------------------------------------------------------

Detect patterns where:

- Delta written
- Immediately read
- Converted to JSON
- Written to Mongo

OR

- Delta written
- Read
- Converted to Pandas
- Written to Excel

For each:
- Flag as avoidable materialization
- Estimate per-job overhead
- Suggest direct in-memory alternative

